<topic id="reset-options">
  <title>Reset Global Options</title><prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Configure the Application<indexterm>reset global options</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To reset all global preferences to their default values you have to go to menu <menucascade>
        <uicontrol product="editor author svnClient diff developer">Options</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol product="editorEclipse authorEclipse developerEclipse">Window</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol product="editorEclipse authorEclipse developerEclipse">Preferences</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol product="editor author svnClient diff developer">Reset Global Options</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol product="editorEclipse developerEclipse">oXygen XML Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol product="authorEclipse">Author</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Reset Global Options</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>. <ph
        product="editor author developer editorEclipse authorEclipse
      developerEclipse">. <ph
          product="editor author developer">The project level preferences are not changed by this
          action.</ph> The list of transformation scenarios will be reset to the default
        scenarios.</ph></p>
  </body>
